## Key Points

The Power of Flawless Migrations: Incapsula used SEO as its primary growth engine, scaling from 20,000 to 145,000 monthly organic visitors. When acquired by Imperva, they preserved all that equity by executing nearly 3,500 precise, 1-to-1 301 redirects, instantly boosting Imperva’s traffic from 12k to 286k monthly visitors.

Comprehensive Topical Authority: They didn't just write a few articles; they built a massive content hub covering almost every IT security topic (phishing, IP spoofing, firewalls). This resulted in roughly 1,600 pages ranking on the first page of Google.

Aggressive CRO on Informational Content: They turned high-traffic blog posts into lead generators by layering multiple CTAs (demo requests, live chat, gated free reports, and exit-intent popups). This multi-touch approach yields an estimated 2-4% conversion rate on organic traffic.

Contextual Backlink Building: Ranking for highly competitive terms wasn't accidental. Their team actively built contextual backlinks through guest posts and outreach, securing hundreds of referring domains for their core pillar pages to push them to the top of the SERPs.